The db/index.ts also has the same issue - it doesn't check the success field of the yaml.write calls and assumes they'll always succeed.

But wait - the `yaml:write` handler in the main process doesn't actually return the success field as a checked result in the renderer. Let me look again:

The main process handler (yamlService.ts line 63):
```typescript
ipcMain.handle('yaml:write', async (_event, filePath: string, data: any): Promise<{ success: boolean; error?: string }> => {
    try {
      ...
      fs.writeFileSync(validation.resolvedPath!, yamlStr, 'utf-8')
      return { success: true }
    } catch (e: any) {
      return { success: false, error: `YAML 写入失败: ${e.message}` }
    }
  })
```

So it returns `{ success: true }` or `{ success: false, error: '...' }`. The call site in the renderer does `await window.electronAPI.yaml.write(...)` - this awaits the promise returned by `ipcRenderer.invoke`, which resolves to the return value of the handler. So `await window.electronAPI.yaml.write(...)` would return `{ success: boolean, error?: string }`.

But the FactsPanel code doesn't check this - it just awaits and shows success. This is a bug - if the write fails and returns `{ success: false }`, the code would still show `message.success('伏笔已添加')`.

Let me fix this in FactsPanel.tsx and db/index.ts.

